This data analysis summarizes the Business Development & Expansion Analysis for the MLB portion of the team surveys. The following information can be interpreted from the data.

* Which exclusives or partnerships are ending soon, and what categories do they belong to?  
  * The exclusive/partnerships ending soon include:   
    * Adding new limited partner to ownership groups  
    * Diamond Kinetics  
    * BETMGM  
    * Jersey patches with St. Louis based Stifel and Marketing Partnership  
    * Hot Dogs  
    * Mynd  
  * The partnership categories that are ending soon include investment, Baseball Training Academy, Betting, Marketing, a food category, and a pouring partner.  
* What categories are listed under “non-exclusive” that venues are actively seeking new business for?  
  * The “non-exclusive” categories are Convenience Stores, Grocery Partners, Food Distributors, Pouring Partners, and Wireless Networks  
* Is there alignment between non-exclusive searches and categories with low sponsorship saturation?  
  * Not Enough Data.  
* Which venues control their own media (TV/radio), indicating opportunities for direct partnership or ad placements?  
  * 6 baseball stadiums control their own media, including the Kauffman Stadium (Kansas City Royals Home), Truist Park (Atlanta Braves Home), Busch Stadium (St. Louis Cardinals Home), Wrigley Field (Chicago Cubs Home), T-Mobile Park (Seattle Mariners Home), and Petco Park (San Diego Padres Home).  
* Track upcoming contract expirations. These represent windows to pitch new sponsorships.  
  * Not Enough Data.  
1. Ending Exclusive Partnership Categories

   Which exclusives or partnerships are ending soon?![][image1]

According to the data, each baseball team that answered the question has different annual exclusive partnerships.  The majority of these teams will be ending their sponsorships soon.  Specifically, on September 28, 2025\.  These teams include:

* The Philadelphia Phillies  
* The Pittsburgh Pirates  
* The Cincinnati Reds  
* The Miami Marlins  
* Chicago Cubs

Note: The St. Louis Cardinals signed a 7-year long partnership in 2023 for jersey patches, which will not end until 2030\.

1.2 What categories do they belong to?

As each team gave a different answer, the categories are all different as well, they include baseball training, betting, food, investment, marketing, and pouring/beverage.

4. Media Control

   Which venues control their own media (TV/radio), indicating opportunities for direct partnership or ad placements?![][image10]

   ![][image11]

According to the data, 6 out of the 29 baseball stadiums that have answered this question are in control of their media, including Kauffman Stadium (Kansas City Royals Home), Truist Park(Atlanta Braves Home), Busch Stadium (St. Louis Cardinals Home), Wrigley Field (Chicago Cubs Home), T-Mobile Park (Seattle Mariners Home), and Petco Park (San Diego Padres Home). This means that these stadiums are looking for opportunities to directly partner with a sponsor and place ads.
